SIMPLE: superadd
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Superadd
<hw>Su`per*add"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Superadded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Superadding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>superaddere</ets>.
See <er>Super-</er>, and <er>Add</er>.]</ety> <def>To add over and
above; to add to what has been added; to annex, as something
extrinsic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The strength of any living creature, in those external motion, is
something distinct from, and <qex>superadded</qex> unto, its natural
gravity.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Wilkins.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The peacock laid it extremely to heart that he had not the
nightingale's voice <qex>superadded</qex> to the beauty of his
plumes.</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Superaddition</ent>⟦br⟧
